# CLAUDE.local.md (example — copy to CLAUDE.local.md, which is gitignored)

Private, identifying context that must never land in the public repo:
real name, employer, specific account nicknames, family/team member names,
anything that ties this project to a real person or organization.

Copy this file to `CLAUDE.local.md` (same directory) and fill it in. It is
loaded automatically via the `@CLAUDE.local.md` import in `CLAUDE.md` — no
other wiring needed. If the file doesn't exist, that import is just a no-op.

---

## Who this is for

- Owner's name: <fill in>
- This is a personal project, unrelated to <employer name>. No
  <employer>-issued accounts, infra, JIRA, or <employer>-bound MCPs/
  connectors (e.g. a Google Drive/Gmail connector logged in under a work
  identity) should touch this project's data. Flag any leakage immediately.

## GitHub identity for this repo

- Local git identity + SSH key setup used so commits/pushes here are
  attributed to the project's own GitHub identity, never the owner's
  personal one. (Document the actual key path / SSH host alias here.)

## Real Wallet account names worth knowing

- Public docs generalize account names where they'd otherwise reveal a
  first name (e.g. "the second Raiffeisen credit card" instead of its real
  in-app nickname). If you need the exact live name, check the Wallet MCP
  directly — don't restore it into tracked docs.
